# **VI S√òGER STATISTER **

Vi s√∏ger featured statister M/K/NB i alderen 28-45 til en kortfilm af Agnes Trier. Castet inkluderer Filippa Coster-Waldau, Jacob Lohmann, Olivia Joof, Sidsel Siem Koch og Kitt Maiken Mortensen. 

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

Tristans mor er en karakterunders√∏gelse af en ung kvinde i en s√•rbar periode.

Praktisk info:

Du skal spille en for√¶ldre i for√¶ldregruppen, s√• det vigtigt du kan deltage i optagelser hele dagen d. 24/1+25/1 i tidsrummet 8-18, og meget gerne ogs√• en halv dag i aftentimerne mandag. d. 26/1.

Erfaring med improvisation og replikker er en fordel, men ikke et 

krav.

Jobbet er ul√∏nnet men vi s√∏ger for forplejning og god energi. 

Vi filmer i Sydhavnen.

Ved interesse send vellignende billede, samt navn, alder og erfaring til casting@adomeitfilm.com

items.text:
Some of you aren‚Äôt booking from self-tapes for one simple reason‚Ä¶

You‚Äôre not working hard enough on them.

And I‚Äôm not even talking about training.

I‚Äôm talking about:

‚úÖ Not getting emotionally ready
‚úÖ Not getting physically ready
‚úÖ Not building the stakes properly
‚úÖ Not doing the inner work before you hit record
‚úÖ Hoping it‚Äôll be ‚Äúgood enough‚Äù

Let me be clear‚Ä¶

‚ÄúGood enough‚Äù doesn‚Äôt book jobs.

Casting can smell it a mile off when:
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt created a real life-or-death urgency
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt committed to a truth
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt built pressure
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt connected to the why

If your character doesn‚Äôt NEED something‚Ä¶
casting won‚Äôt NEED you.

So next time you tape ‚Äî don‚Äôt just learn lines.

Prepare like it‚Äôs the only shot you‚Äôve got.
Because it might be.

üëá Want to find out more?

Vom 09.02.2026 - 22.05.2026 findet in der Schnitt-Akademie Berlin der n√§chste gro√üe Kompaktkurs Filmschnitt f√ºr alle statt, die sich in den technischen und dramaturgischen Bereichen des Filmschnitts weiterbilden wollen: https://www.schnitt-akademie.de/kompaktkurse.php?KursID=100

Der Kurs findet komplett in Form von Online-Unterricht statt, man kann also von jedem beliebigen Ort aus daran teilnehmen. Er dauert 3,5 Monate, Mo-Fr jeweils von 09:00-17:00. 

**Die Weiterbildung kann mit einem Bildungsgutschein der Agentur f√ºr Arbeit (100%-F√∂rderung, auch f√ºr Firmen und Besch√§ftigte) oder durch die EU-F√∂rderung KOMPASS (90%-F√∂rderung, f√ºr Solo-Selbst√§ndige) finanziert werden .** 

Inhalte des Kurses: 

- AVID Mediacomposer

- DaVinci Resolve

- Adobe Premiere Pro

- After Effects

- Spiel- u. Dokumentarfilmschnitt

- Schnitt von TV-News und Reportagen

- Codecs, Imports, Exports und Workflows

- Schnitt u. Sound

- Dramaturgie, Rhythmus und Gestaltung

- Schnitt-Assistenz

- Musikschnitt

- Colorgrading

- Vertrags- u. Urheberrecht

Die Anmeldung l√§uft, es gibt zur Zeit noch Pl√§tze: https://www.schnitt-akademie.de/kompaktkurse.php?KursID=100

We are a here for budding actors and anyone else looking to work in the film industry. 

As a collective we use budding actors, sound crew, lighting crew, camera operators, script writers, editors, directors, continuity, props and any other department in film making and the idea is we all work together, help each other to produce content that helps in your journey.

**‚ÄºÔ∏èCASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT FILM ‚ÄúTHE TREE‚Äù (NORTH WEST LONDON)üé¨**

We‚Äôre currently casting for the upcoming sci-fi short film ***The Tree***, shooting in **Bovingdon**, starting **26th February**.

**We are a low-budget production, so paid roles will be a flat-rate and TBD during interview. We will also consider actors with little to no experience on an expenses-only basis. **

**Looking for actors based in:**

London, Hertfordshire, Oxford, Reading, Milton Keynes and surrounding areas.

**Roles needed:**

* **EVE (YOUNG ACTRESS) *****(7-10 years, she/her)*****: average height, blonde hair, blue eyes.** Open to any and all young actors capable of portraying a child kept in captivity, **with a parent/guardian who can act as their on-set chaperone.**

* **EVE (TEEN/ADULT) *****(teens/early 20s, she/her)*****: female; blonde hair; blue eyes.** An emotionally complex young woman who has never experienced the outside world. She is curious, eager and desperate to break free from her confinement. She exhibits a mix of innocence and intense longing, and as such needs to convey isolation and hope.

* **SCIENTIST (*****late 30‚Äôs-50‚Äôs, he/him*****): male, caucasian, any hair/eye colour. **A reclusive scientist who has kept his teenage daughter in captivity to genetically engineer her survival in a toxic, post-apocalyptic world. Isolated and grieving his late wife, he struggles with guilt, lonliness, and a strained relationship with his daughter. 

* **DAN *****(25-35, he/him)*****: male, tall, any hair/eye colour, any/all ethnicities.** Dan is an intimidating and opportunistic man living in a post-apocalyptic world. He is untrustworthy and takes advantage of vulnerable people for his own gain. The character uses manipulation to get what he wants, but his true intentions are always self-serving and often sinister.

Filming will take place **entirely in Bovingdon and London**. Actors must be able to communte to both on a reliable basis.

To apply, please email **both**:

**[finlayandrews01@gmail.com](mailto:finlayandrews01@gmail.com)**** and ****[meg.ramdenee@gmail.com](mailto:meg.ramdenee@gmail.com)**

Include:

* Name
* Age
* Recent photo/headshot
* Link to monologue/scene recording of your choice (preferred)

Please feel free to share with anyone who may be interested. Open to all experience levels. Thank you! üé¨

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì UK FEATURE FILM
LUCY HARDING

(Supporting Role)

Fire in the Hole Productions are casting Lucy Harding for the independent British crime drama IMPROPER BASTARDS.

Lucy is Danny Fincher‚Äôs former partner and the mother of his son. Their relationship was intense and defining ‚Äî and its collapse left lasting damage on both sides. She made the decision to leave, and she lives with the consequences of that choice every day.

She carries guilt surrounding the loss of their child, but she does not wear it openly. Lucy‚Äôs strength lies in containment. She has rebuilt her life carefully and is determined not to be pulled back into chaos ‚Äî even when Danny‚Äôs return threatens everything she has stabilised.

This is a role rooted in emotional restraint, moral complexity, and inner conflict.

Lucy does not plead, rage, or unravel. She sets boundaries. She holds her ground. The emotion lives beneath the surface.

üé≠ ROLE REQUIREMENTS

Female, White British

Playing age: Early 30s ‚Äì very early 40s

Accent: London or Southern British (essential)

Appearance: Natural, grounded, attractive

Role Type: Supporting

We are looking for an actress capable of subtle, psychologically truthful screen work ‚Äî someone comfortable allowing silence, subtext, and history to do the work.

üé• PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE (ESSENTIAL)

This role requires:

A professional actress

Feature film experience

Spotlight listing

A strong, naturalistic showreel

This is not a role for short-film-only performers, students, or first feature credits.

üé¨ PRODUCTION DETAILS

Production: Improper Bastards

Production Company: Fire in the Hole Productions

Format: Independent UK Feature Film

Payment: Paid role (expenses covered)

Credit: IMDb credit

Filming Location: East Sussex

Schedule: Mid-April ‚Äì early June (dates TBC)

üì© SUBMISSIONS

Please submit:

Headshot

CV and Spotlight link

Showreel (essential)

üìß hello@fireintheholeproductionsfilms.com

This role will be listed on Spotlight and professional casting platforms. We are sharing it here to reach experienced actresses drawn to serious, character-driven crime drama.

üé¨ NOTES

No clich√©s.

No melodrama.

No victim narratives.

This is adult storytelling ‚Äî grounded, restrained, and emotionally honest.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Diaspora

We are casting for a short narrative film titled Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Diaspora is set in 1970s Britain and follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport, whose encounter with a Balkan-born photographer leads both men to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. Set largely within a photography studio, the film is intimate and character-driven, relying on subtle performance, quiet tension, and emotional restraint.

This is an intimate short film exploring displacement, identity in transition, and the unspoken grief carried by those who leave their homeland. 

Filming will take place in Bristol and surrounding areas in early March (exact dates TBC). This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided. The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

We are looking for performers who feel natural, emotionally grounded, and sensitive to character, with the ability to convey internal states through stillness and small gestures.

To apply:ÔøΩPlease send a headshot and CV to diasporafilm2026@gmail.com

THE PHOTOGRAPHER: Male, late A who fled his homeland years ago. Emotionally guarded, keeps clients distance until he recognises something familiar Ali's struggle. To apply, send headshots & CV's to dliasporaim2026agrmail.com Filming Bristol Surrounding areas Early March dates TBC. Seeking contributors travel expenses and food will be provided.'

üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì ‚ÄòGaffa Cakes‚Äô Short Commercial 

We are casting for a short, character-driven commercial being made as part of our final year on the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Concept: 
Set inside a football changing room, the commercial follows an explosive football manager at breaking point. Built around heightened behaviour and recognisable football culture, the piece uses comedy and character to capture a moment where anger gives way to something unexpected.

Role ‚Äì 
Football Manager (Lead): We‚Äôre looking for a performer to play a stereotypical angry football gaffer ‚Äî loud, intense, and emotionally charged. The role is performance-led, combining dialogue, physicality, and strong character presence. Think Steve Bracknall, with familiar touchline anger and intensity.

Filming: Bristol, w/c 2nd February (exact date TBC)

This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided, and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

To apply: Please send headshots and CVs to scarlet2.gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Seeking contributors voluntarily- travel expenses and food will be provided. TO APPLY, SEND HEADSHOTS & CV'S S TO SCARLET2 CARLET2.GERRY@LIVE.UWEAC.U GERRY@LIVE. UWE AC.UK'

items.text:
Hey everyone!

We are now casting **non-union actors** for *An Empty Cup*, a satirical dramedy student short film supported by Vancouver Film School.

This is a **student-led, non-union volunteer production**. While unpaid, the project includes full craft services, catering, and a complimentary professional headshot session for selected performers.

Self-tape submissions open **January 14 at 9:00 AM** and close **January 24 at 11:00 PM**. In-person callbacks will be held on **January 26 from 12:00 PM to 4:00 PM**.

Filming is scheduled for **February 7‚Äì8, 2026** in the **Greater Vancouver Area**.

We are seeking talent for multiple roles with **open ethnicity casting** and encourage performers of all backgrounds to submit. Below, the synopsis of the film and roles of each character are posted.

For more information, please visit our Instagram (@anemptycup_film) or email us at anemptycupfilm@gmail.com.

-An Empty Cup Crew

Some of you aren‚Äôt booking from self-tapes for one simple reason‚Ä¶

You‚Äôre not working hard enough on them.

And I‚Äôm not even talking about training.

I‚Äôm talking about:

‚úÖ Not getting emotionally ready
‚úÖ Not getting physically ready
‚úÖ Not building the stakes properly
‚úÖ Not doing the inner work before you hit record
‚úÖ Hoping it‚Äôll be ‚Äúgood enough‚Äù

Let me be clear‚Ä¶

‚ÄúGood enough‚Äù doesn‚Äôt book jobs.

Casting can smell it a mile off when:
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt created a real life-or-death urgency
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt committed to a truth
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt built pressure
 ‚Ä¢ you haven‚Äôt connected to the why

If your character doesn‚Äôt NEED something‚Ä¶
casting won‚Äôt NEED you.

So next time you tape ‚Äî don‚Äôt just learn lines.

- The Breath Reset - Live Webinar Jan. 22 (tomorrow!) 

One of the fastest ways to get out of your head and back into the work is also the most overlooked tool we have: the breath.

Before you go searching for a new choice, pause.

Right now‚Äîwherever you are‚Äîtake a breath in.
Good.
Take another.

Now notice what comes up.
Notice where that breath takes you.
Whatever response you have is organic. It‚Äôs present. It‚Äôs happening to you in real time.

That response is already more usable than any idea you have about how you should be feeling in the moment.

Biochemically, you‚Äôre no longer in the same state. Your nervous system has shifted. Heart rate, hormones, internal rhythm‚Äîall adjusted. A breath changes the conditions.

This is why we work with breath in the 90-Day Accelerator‚Äînot as a relaxation exercise, but as a professional reset.

Many actors think they need to consciously manufacture a more dynamic choice. But very often the issue isn‚Äôt imagination‚Äîit‚Äôs self-consciousness. Trying. Monitoring. Performing.

A breath interrupts that.

It reminds your body that you‚Äôre alive, that you‚Äôre real, and that the other person is real too. From that place, behavior becomes available again.

So the next time you feel stuck, blank, or ‚Äúoff‚Äù in a scene‚Äîdon‚Äôt force it.

Take a breath.
See what happens.
Respond.

Presence beats planning‚Äîevery time.

Actors ‚Äî if you‚Äôre serious about 2026, read this.

I‚Äôm hosting a live ‚ÄúElevate Your Acting Career in 2026‚Äù webinar ‚Äî ***the only way to work with me outside of my 90-Day Coaching Conservatory.

We‚Äôll break down:
‚Ä¢ What actually moves the needle in today‚Äôs industry
‚Ä¢ The difference between instinct vs. intuition (and why confusing the two holds actors back)
‚Ä¢ How to prepare, audition, and position yourself so you‚Äôre not competing ‚Äî you‚Äôre clear

üóì Jan 22
‚è∞ 10am PST / 1pm EST
üíª Live, immersive, 2.5 hrs
üí∞ $99 working actors | $50 interactive audit (limited)

DM or email george@theactorsinstinct.com to reserve your spot.

Spots are limited. Clarity beats hope. Always.

From online premieres to casting decisions based on audience reach, the line between talent and producer is gone. Watch to learn how to position yourself in this new era of filmmaking.

items.text:
Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: ‚ÄúThe Balled of Crooked Lane‚Äù by Tom Mclennan and ‚ÄúWake‚Äù by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

üé•CASTING CALL ‚Äî WAR-TIME DRAMA SHORT FILM

We are casting Enemy Soldiers and Civilians for an intense, large-scale Field Hospital sequence in a war-time drama short film.

üìÖ January 24‚Äì25 (primarily Sunday, January 25)
üìç Big Dalton, Glendora

The film follows a teenage girl forced into adulthood while trying to survive in the midst of war. This Field Hospital scene is a major turning point: civilians gather at night believing they are safe, when a sudden enemy attack erupts and everything collapses into chaos.

We are looking for as many people as possible to create a crowded, immersive environment. This is a physically active, emotionally intense scene involving movement, urgency, and controlled chaos.

Details:
 ‚Ä¢ One-day, non-paid role
 ‚Ä¢ Food provided
 ‚Ä¢ Film credit + copy of the film provided
 ‚Ä¢ Seeking White / European actors

If you‚Äôre interested or know someone who might be, please contact tancproduction@gmail.com 

Our film website: https://tancproduction.netlify.app/#support

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

message.text:
A glimpse into my journey, my range, and the stories I‚Äôve had the honor to bring to life. Each role stretched me, challenged me, and reminded me why I fell in love with storytelling in the first place.

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day.

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

**Marketing Interns: Your Next Big Opportunity is Here! üöÄ**

**Kandid Media** is urgently seeking dynamic and driven **Marketing Interns** to join our fast-paced team for a 60-day intensive program.

This isn't just about fetching coffee‚Äîit's about diving headfirst into real-world media strategy, content creation, and campaign execution. If you're ready to learn, innovate, and make a tangible impact, this is your shot.

**The Pathway:** We believe in rewarding talent and hard work. After a successful 60-day internship, top performers will be invited to transition into a **paid part-time position** with Kandid Media. This is your chance to turn passion into profession.

**We're looking for individuals who are:**
* Eager to learn about media, content strategy, and digital marketing.
* Proactive, creative, and reliable.
* Ready to contribute to a growing media company.

**Why Join Kandid Media?** You'll work alongside experienced professionals, gain invaluable hands-on experience, and contribute to projects that span film, branded content, and community-driven initiatives. This is about building your resume with real results and securing your future in the industry.

**Apply Now: Send us a DM with a brief overview of your marketing interest/experience and what social platforms you have the greatest knowledge in. **

We're moving fast, so don't delay!

Casting call - Stray Dog
Currently casting all roles for 10 minute graduate film based in Bristol and surrounding areas. 

Set in the 1930‚Äôs, Stray Dog follows two silent cinema owning brothers during the rise of the ‚ÄúTalkies‚Äù. Oz leaves his brother and sets up his travelling cinema with lover Nancy. They party and discover how it feels to be free, but grow apart when Oz can‚Äôt learn to be serious. Eventually, a car crash allows Oz to come to terms with who he‚Äôs become and reflect on the important things in life. 

As it‚Äôs a student film, we are seeking contributors on a voluntary basis, but food and travel expenses will be covered. 

Shoot length is a maximum of 5 days, and will take place between end of February and start of March (dates TBC). 

We would love to hear from you! Please email: ttpsfilm@yahoo.com

Comedy short film - 10 minutes 

A struggling theater show is made worse by a new member of the crew who‚Äôs inexperience makes it a night to remember.

Lee (male 20-30)

An ambitious theatre worker who is always wanting more out of life. Can be naive to the ways of the world but has blind optimism that gets him

A sarcastic, hardworking tech worker who struggles to find joy from his work. Wants to use his talents elsewhere but has no motivation to do so.

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì A PLACE NOT MINE** üé≠

We are casting for **A Place Not Mine**, a new original musical (cabaret style) exploring **belonging, identity, and chosen family**, set in a magical university world.

‚ú® **FINAL ROLE AVAILABLE** ‚ú®

‚ú® **ORIS** (Male, playing age 20‚Äì24)

üìç **Performance Dates:**
**5th & 6th July**
üìç **Drayton Arms Theatre**, London

üìç **Rehearsals:**
Late February / Early March
Approximately **one rehearsal per week**, scheduled around cast availability

üé≠ **Project Type:** Showcase production
This version of the project is **unpaid**, with the aim of documenting the work and sharing it with theatre makers and creatives. All performers will receive a **professional video recording of their performance** for personal use and showreels.

üì© **To apply:**
Please send your **CV / headshot** and a short introduction to:

ACTING IN LONG-FORM IMPROV
3-Hour Intensive with Arek Ziƒôtek
Go deeper into story, character, and relationships.
For improvisers with basic experience and curious newcomers ready to play.
This is a focused intensive (not a jam).
We move from core principles to advanced long-form tools, blending acting craft with improvisation to create grounded, honest scenes.
You‚Äôll work on:
‚Ä¢ Building believable characters in the moment
‚Ä¢ Emotional truth & listening
‚Ä¢ Relationships that drive long-form stories
‚Ä¢ Presence, commitment & clarity on stage
‚Ä¢ Sustaining scenes beyond jokes
Acting first. Comedy second. Real, playful, alive.
With Arek Ziƒôtek
Warsaw-based theatre teacher, trained in the Keith Johnstone tradition (Theatresports)

‚è∞ 2:00‚Äì5:00 PM
üìç Po≈Çudnik 2.0 ¬∑ Wilcza 25, Warsaw

CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
‚Ä¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"
‚Ä¢ Type: Short
‚Ä¢ Location: Boulder, CO
‚Ä¢ Compensation: $50 (negotiable), lunch provided
‚Ä¢ Time Commitment: 2 half-days (3-5 hours)

SYNOPSIS
Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ The Contractor: Male, 28-45+
A contract killer. Stoic, calculating, and cold-blooded; or at least that how he seems. Unknown to his client, he is secretly working for the police, undercover as a hitman.

‚Ä¢ Detective Moss: Female, 30s+
An interrogator who knows how to get a confession without raising her voice. But she doesn't just want to prove guilt: she wants to know why.

TO SUBMIT:
‚Ä¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition.
‚Ä¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush" 

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì ‚ÄòGaffa Cakes‚Äô Short Commercial 

We are casting for a short, character-driven commercial being made as part of our final year on the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Concept: 
Set inside a football changing room, the commercial follows an explosive football manager at breaking point. Built around heightened behaviour and recognisable football culture, the piece uses comedy and character to capture a moment where anger gives way to something unexpected.

Role ‚Äì 
Football Manager (Lead): We‚Äôre looking for a performer to play a stereotypical angry football gaffer ‚Äî loud, intense, and emotionally charged. The role is performance-led, combining dialogue, physicality, and strong character presence. Think Steve Bracknall, with familiar touchline anger and intensity.

Filming: Bristol, w/c 2nd February (exact date TBC)

This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided, and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

To apply: Please send headshots and CVs to scarlet2.gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

üé≠ CASTING CALL ‚Äì EXPERIENCED ENTERTAINERS (ONGOING WORK)
This SATURDAY ‚Äì LONDON

Genome Theatre is looking for exceptional, experienced children‚Äôs entertainers to join our growing team.

Roles needed THIS SATURDAY:

‚ú® Ariel
‚ú® Moana

This is well paid work with the potential for regular ongoing bookings.

About us

Genome Theatre creates immersive, story-led children‚Äôs parties and experiences - our work goes far beyond a standard party.
Our entertainers are not just hosts, but performers, bringing characters to life through storytelling, play, and theatrical interaction.

We also work across:
 ‚Ä¢ immersive shows
 ‚Ä¢ quests & adventures
 ‚Ä¢ bespoke events

So we‚Äôre looking to build long-term relationships, not just one-off cover.

We‚Äôre looking for:
 ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê Highly experienced children‚Äôs entertainers / performers
 ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê Confident character portrayal (voice, energy, storytelling)
 ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê Warm, engaging, and excellent with children
 ‚Ä¢ ‚≠ê Reliable, professional, and calm under pressure

This is not entry-level party work.

What we offer:
 ‚Ä¢ Competitive pay
 ‚Ä¢ Supportive, creative team
 ‚Ä¢ Beautiful, well-run events
 ‚Ä¢ Opportunities for ongoing work across multiple formats

How to apply:

Please DM / email info@genometheatre.co.uk with:
 ‚Ä¢ Your name
 ‚Ä¢ Which character(s) you can play
 ‚Ä¢ Spotlight/Mandy link or CV
 ‚Ä¢ Your experience with children‚Äôs parties / performance

üìç London-based performers
üóì Availability this Saturday essential

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara CioazƒÉ and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

Posting this for a filmmaker friend.  Contact him (not me) directly.  "I am creating a pitch deck for a pilot I‚Äôve written and I need an actress or model with extensive dramatic training to portray my lead character in costume.

The character: A late teenage (17-20) British girl. Minors may apply but a guardian MUST be present on phone calls and at all times we are working together. You‚Äôll be angry, fearful and even a seductress all while brandishing a long sword and a flintlock pistol as you will be portraying a female pirate! This pirate passed herself as a male so we will need to get creative to portray that aspect as well. I will share some of my writing ahead of time so you can prepare.

The work: I‚Äôll need you to meet me for a costume fitting likely in Chicago‚Äôs Lincoln Park but that is still TBD. The shoot will take place that same day or the next day (in the west suburbs) for at most 1 ‚Äì 1.5 hours (depending on costume changes) for an indoor photo shoot. I did this shoot once before and we were done in an hour.

The pay: $150 for the shoot plus expenses for travel to the costume fitting."

How to apply: Send a few pictures including at least one recent head shot to: 
Email: dshayatovich@gmail.com. Subject line: Secret of the Sea Photoshoot

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äî LOS ANGELES
We are casting actors for a vertical drama / short-form series shooting in Los Angeles.

üìÖ Shoot dates: February 2‚Äì5, 2026  

üìç Location: Los Angeles, CA  

üé• Format: Vertical series (mobile drama)

---

### üé≠ ROLES (ADULT ROLES ONLY):
